### A17U — CapitaLand Ascendas REIT | **ADD**

**Price:** SGD 2.52 | **Forward yield:** ~5.93% | **Next results:** 5 May 2026

CLAR remains Singapore's premier industrial-and-logistics REIT with 222 properties across four continents, occupancy above 90%, and positive double-digit rental reversions in FY2025. The 1.3% dip in DPU to 15.005¢ was entirely mechanical (dilution from the June 2025 equity raise) rather than operational, and distributable income actually grew 1.4%. At SGD 2.52, the unit is trading below most analyst fair-value estimates, offering a near-6% forward yield supported by data-centre and logistics tailwinds. With Q2 2026 results due 5 May, there is a near-term catalyst. The position size (4,460 units; SGD 11.2k) is modest relative to the long-term income objective — adding further on any pre-results dip toward SGD 2.40–2.45 makes sense.

---

### C52 — ComfortDelGro | **ADD**

**Price:** SGD 1.48 | **Consensus target:** SGD 1.633 (+10.3%) | **Ex-div:** 4 May 2026 (SGD 0.046)

ComfortDelGro offers an attractive combination of a ~5.7–6.1% dividend yield and double-digit price upside to the SGD 1.633 consensus target. The upcoming SGD 0.046 interim dividend (ex-date 4 May 2026) provides an imminent income event — the stock should be held through ex-date to capture it. The company recently reshuffled its board following the passing of a director, but there is no operational read-through from that change. The transportation business continues to benefit from stable public transit ridership and international operations; full-year 2026 results are not due until August, so there are no short-term earnings landmines. At 3,000 units (SGD 4.4k), this is the smallest SGX position and warrants topping up to build meaningful dividend income.

