### Z74 — Singtel | **HOLD**

**Price:** SGD 4.81 | **Forward yield:** ~3.4–3.8% | **Recent dividend paid:** 18 Apr 2026

Singtel's 2026 DPS is forecast to step down slightly to SGD 0.13 (from ~SGD 0.146 in FY2025), dragging the forward yield to ~2.7–3.4% depending on which measure you use — materially lower than A17U and C52. The stock has recovered significantly (trading near multi-year highs at SGD 4.81) on the back of regional associate recoveries (AIS Thailand, Bharti Airtel India) and internal digital transformation. Given that the holding is 6,342 units (SGD 30.5k — the largest SGX position), and the forward yield has compressed to the lower end of the SGX dividend spectrum, there is no compelling reason to add here. Hold for income continuity and optionality on the value-realisation dividend programme, but recycle incremental capital into higher-yielding SGX names.

