Only 6 units (SGD 1,621) — a very small position. NVDA hit a new 52-week high of USD 216.83 on 28 April before pulling back to USD 210.96 on the 30th. FY2026 revenue came in at a record USD 215.9B (+65% YoY), driven by Data Centre at +75%. The AI infrastructure spending cycle shows no signs of slowing. The position is too small to trim meaningfully — hold and let it run. Next earnings: Q1 FY2027 on 20 May 2026.

